race.comment: JOHNNY (8) tackled the $250k Sunlight Consolation when resuming from a spell last start and did a good job to work home into fourth over 1100m on the Gold Coast. Nicely drawn and will relish the extra 150m this evening. Has the right credentials to take this out. Waterhouse/Bott scratch the pre-post favourite which will help the cause of stablemate WATSON (10) who returned with a win recently, crossing from the outside gate to lead and dominate over 1300m at Kembla. Tackling a far better race this time but on the limit he can run a cheeky race. ZALE (4) made it four wins from his last six outings when the easy winner of a 1200m Cowra open handicap last start. Molly Bourke has a terrific affiliation with the gelding and she stays aboard. Must be respected at a big price. CALGA POWER (6) is racing well including a handy fourth over 1200m at the Kensington track last start. Honest and should be about the money again. The progressive EXTRA HEIGHTS (7) is also in the mix.
